The test can be done on blood or respiratory samples.
Results are usually available within a few hours or days.
This test is usually performed with a nasopharyngeal hisope, although a hisope for the throat can also be used. Some laboratories and companies are developing serological tests, which detect antibodies.
As of April 6, 2020, none of these proved to be accurate enough to allow its widespread use to be approved.
